        "author": {
          "name": "Martin Lizon",
          "email": "martin_lizon@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2012-10-11 14:35:42.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Martin Lizon",
          "email": "martin_lizon@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2012-10-18 18:05:48.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-2028 lnet: Potential data corruption in 'o2iblnd'",
        "message": "LU-2028 lnet: Potential data corruption in 'o2iblnd'\n\nPotential data corruption in 'o2iblnd' (the IB LND driver)\nwhen using pre-mapped DMA buffers\n\nImplemented 'kiblnd_dma_sync_single_for_cpu/device' wrappers\ndepending on whether or not 'HAVE_OFED_IB_DMA_MAP' is defined.\nAdded the call 'kiblnd_dma_sync_single_for_cpu' in 'kiblnd_unmap_tx'.\nThis is the most appropriate place to make the call, as at the time of\nthis call, the device has completed accessing this DMA area, and\nbefore it will access it again to stream the next message.\nAdded the call 'kiblnd_dma_sync_single_for_device' in\n'kiblnd_post_tx_locked', just before calling the IB API function\n'ib_post_send'. This ensures that ownership of the DMA-mapped\nmemory region is handed over to the IB device, at the latest possible\nmoment.\nSimilarly, added dma_sync_single_for_[cpu|device] for 'rx_msg',\nto ensure that transfer of ownership of that DMA-mapped memory\nis transferred at the right time between the CPU and device.\n\nTest-Parameters: nettypes=o2ib\nSigned-off-by: Martin Lizon <martin_lizon@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Nic Henke <nic_henke@xyratex.com>\nReviewed-by: Iurii Golovach <iurii_golovach@xyratex.com>\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-559\nChange-Id: Id74aceadfb7e8f7b749378d2b1eea8bed727f7d9\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
